post_text:
Lamoni Demon Fans & Community:
Friday, Sept. 11th Lamoni will play a varsity football game @ Mormon Trail (Humeston) 7:00 p.m. The Mormon Trail district and surrounding area recently suffered the tragic loss of a three-year-old boys life. Tomorrow evening, they will be honoring this boy by wearing the color "John Deere" Green, his favorite color. The Lamoni school and community does a fantastic job supporting other small communities. We are asking for our Demon fans to show up in green shirts/attire in support of the entire Mormon Trail community as they try to cope with this loss.

Thank you.

post_text:
Guidelines for tonight's volleyball game at Orient-Macksburg

1. Masks are required for all spectators. Please let your parents know.
2. The first two rows of bleachers will not be occupied and the area around the score table will be marked off. Remember to practice social distancing.
3. Restrooms will be limited to 3 people. We have restrooms on both sides in the East and West hallways.
4. Students 6th grade and younger are required to sit with their parents.
5. Exact change if possible. $5 adults and $3 students for varsity and $3 adults and $2 students for junior high.
6. There will be concessions available.

post_text:
EMS Experience Workshop
Thursday July 30, 2020 10-11 AM.

Meeting will be at the EMS/Fire Station at 120 N. Chestnut. Entrance on the north side of the building.

Southwestern Community College and Lamoni EMS will host an Emergency Medical Tech Basic course in Lamoni, during the fall 2020 semester. The EMS Experience Workshop will provide a brief introduction to the course for students interested in enrolling. The primary focus of the emergency medical technician (EMT) is to provide basic emergency medical care and transportation for patients who access the emergency medical system.

post_text: Today the Middle School had its "Holiday Celebration." They turned in food they collected for the Food Pantry of Lamoni (over 300 food items), played some games, read to elementary students, did arts and crafts with the P.T.O., and caroled throughout the community. The students had a great time and a big thanks goes out to all of the volunteers who made today possible. Thank you so much and from the Middle School, happy holidays!

post_text: Lamoni 6th graders recently had a bake sale to raise money for Toys for Tots. We sold baked goods at Middle School Fun Night and again on December 16 during the middle school basketball games. We had a great day of shopping at Dollar General for toys to be donated to Decatur County Toys for Tots. Thank you to everyone who supported our efforts through baking, buying, donating, and helping!

post_text: On December 10th the sixth and seventh grade science classes enjoyed a visit with Hilary and Nate from ISUs Water Rocks! program. The students learned about the value of good soil, the benefits humans receive from good soil, and how to keep the soil in place. Also, the 8th grade science students have been studying ecosystem biodiversity. Here are some of the ecosystems they researched/designed.

post_text: Mrs. Mickelson's kindergarden class using their homemade anemometers. Students studied weather and tools used to measure different types of weather. They made the anemometers to test wind speed using paper plates, cups, and pencils. After going outside to find that it is a calm day, the created their own wind using fans and hairdryers.
text: Mrs. Mickelson's kindergarden class using their homemade anemometers. Students studied weather and tools used to measure different types of weather. They made the anemometers to test wind speed using paper plates, cups, and pencils. After going outside to find that it is a calm day, the created their own wind using fans and hairdryers.

post_text: Yesterday Mrs. Ranney took the 1st grade class to the Lamoni Public Library to see the IPTV STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Mathematics) Bus. The students had a blast exploring STEM (same as above, but without the A) manipulatives, trial and error, and problem solving. Thanks to the Public Library for getting IPTV down here and thanks to IPTV for coming down. They will be in town until the 22nd.

post_text: Mrs. Martin is doing some exciting stuff with the third, fourth, and fifth grades. They are using Quizlet to review and she is teaching them how to create their very own. Quizlet splits the kids into teams and they compete against others to answer whatever questions are part of the quiz. It is a fun way to review, teaches teamwork, and is a good program for the kids to learn to use. Keep up the great work guys!
